Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.22,0:01:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.22,0:01:40.68,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nishi Medical University {Supplementary }Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.53,0:01:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.10,0:01:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata is asleep on drugs now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.25,0:01:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right, the sharp pain \Nseems to have been soothed already.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.01,0:01:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My, isn't it Ranko! What a long time it's been. \NNo less than 5 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.18,0:01:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Katsura?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.55,0:02:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who paired up with Jin in the middle school? \N{\i1}That{\i0} Mr. Katsura Daigo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.66,0:02:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't recognize you at all. \NWith that head...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.01,0:02:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.37,0:02:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,For various reasons, I entered monkhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.68,0:02:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.42,0:02:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, various reasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.71,0:02:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing, compared to what Munakata \Nendured in those 5 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.34,0:02:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, in this 5 years span, even while facing \Nthe despair of death, he never took a single step back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.85,0:02:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He made it all the way to this point. \NTo this point, he never gave up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.29,0:02:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Munakata.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.17,0:02:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.73,0:02:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait. \NWon't you stay by Jin's side until the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.60,0:02:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You are, in fact, Jin's one and only best friend. \NStay by his side, I'm begging you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.30,0:02:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever I go, the pain of parting with Munakata \Nremains unabated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.05,0:02:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Those 5 years I spent in ascetic practices, \Nseeking for strength to endure this pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.58,0:02:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ranko, in my and Munakata's mind, our parting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.70,0:02:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,already happened long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What a stupid joke it must be!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.89,0:03:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hospitalized?{\i0} No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.35,0:03:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.64,0:03:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How could he get hospitalized, \Nif he was so full of energy just yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.49,0:03:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.77,0:03:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hospital! To the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.87,0:03:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Flowers... Right, I must buy some flowers before going!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.49,0:03:27.49,TITLE,,0,0,0,,{\bord4\blur15\3c&HFFC32A&\t(0,1000,\bord0\blur0.4\c&HF2E7E9&)\c&HFEFDFF&\fnGabriola\fs78\pos(320,355)}Episode 2 \N\N\NOka, aim for the ace!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.59,0:03:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi, here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.62,0:03:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, Maki!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.72,0:03:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it you who asked me to wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.18,0:03:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I doing! \NI forgot to buy flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.29,0:03:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You owe me a treat for this. \NI covered Hiromi's part too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.51,0:04:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, what is wrong?{/ what is that plaintive sound?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.71,0:04:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.35,0:04:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, mom, I have a favor, \Nplease don't cry like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.58,0:04:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Jin. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.18,0:04:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?\NWhat became of training schedule?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.73,0:04:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At 10 you're supposed to be on the court \Nto have a 3-set match with Madame B!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.46,0:04:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was it that promised me to win at least once \Nbefore leaving for America?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.29,0:04:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Dry your tears,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.17,0:04:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.16,0:04:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Tears have no meaning! Begone! \NBegone from my sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.73,0:04:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach! Coach on the hospital bed... This is the first time \NI'm seeing something so unimaginable...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.95,0:04:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.20,0:04:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean... Coach hospitalized, what a nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.24,0:04:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa, sorry to bother. \NHere, flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.41,0:04:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Maki, let's return.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.25,0:04:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And... If you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.02,0:05:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin, I'll call her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.71,0:05:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.13,0:05:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgot something, Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.10,0:05:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... Can you tell me your prognosis?{/ I just wanted to know about your condition.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.43,0:05:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to worry. \NDiagnosis is a trifling overwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.85,0:05:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.82,0:05:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Truest ever. In preparation for the trip to America, \Nthey imposed a hospitalization upon me as a precaution.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.13,0:05:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be discharged in a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.61,0:05:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.41,0:05:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I ever lied to you before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.66,0:05:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.81,0:05:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.40,0:05:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.65,0:05:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Excuse us. \N- Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.88,0:05:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oy, what's this all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.55,0:05:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to sabotage everyone's practice \Nwhen we're so close to going to US?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.39,0:05:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.83,0:05:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.80,0:05:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and return to the court. \NStart warming up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.35,0:05:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.41,0:06:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka sure wasn't the only one caught off-guard \Nwith Coach's hospitalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.12,0:06:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad it turned out well, nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.96,0:06:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so. Because actually, \NI tried to meet the doctor attending to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.03,0:06:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what happened is, upon conducting \Na thorough examination, he just got fixated on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.93,0:06:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.37,0:06:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. \NI don't understand this case at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.21,0:06:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Jin, I'll come again \Nfirst thing tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget, the call. Can you do it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.74,0:06:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.57,0:06:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but tonight Jin \Nwants you to come by any means.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.90,0:06:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, all alone{/ by yourself}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.42,0:07:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.09,0:07:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Get closer, I got something for your ears only.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.76,0:07:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My diagnosis is marrow{/ myeloid - this is scientific term he uses, but we're doing tennis drama anime here, not a physician's handbook} leukemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.60,0:07:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It began five years ago, \Nwith no hope for remission.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.89,0:07:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, I was only given 3 years to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.27,0:07:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This body managed to hold on for 5 years instead. \NBut it's finally caving in{/ crumbling}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.16,0:07:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.73,0:07:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If it somehow manages to withstand it once more, \NI may be able to go to America with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All the way until now, by clinging one by one \Nto every hope like that, I kept buying some more time.{/ I kept dragging my life for some more time.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.29,0:07:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But frankly speaking, it's clear to me - \Nthe time has come. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.81,0:07:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.85,0:07:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't spill a word about it to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.46,0:07:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just as a fellow player, \Nbut also as her man, take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.26,0:07:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, the person bound to become the closest to her \Nfrom now on, Todo,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.89,0:07:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is none other than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.93,0:07:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, Oka is your...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.43,0:08:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think this 27 years long life of mine \Nis in any way inferior to that of 80 years.{/ to that of an 80 years old person.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.69,0:08:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Just three years...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.85,0:08:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he really have to pass away already? \NJust some 3 years after he appeared in our lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.15,0:08:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Us - we can probably handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.64,0:08:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, Ozaki and Madame Butterfly - \Nwe were all introduced to tennis long before meeting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.36,0:08:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But what will become of her, Coach?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.87,0:08:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She discovered tennis through you. \NLearned to trust through you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.21,0:08:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And perhaps, even love was revealed to her this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.98,0:08:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What would become of Oka if she's left alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.09,0:08:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's ruthless, Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.39,0:08:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruthless...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.51,0:08:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Katsura Daigo, perhaps,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.96,0:08:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the final letter I will ever write you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.27,0:08:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The final favor I will ask from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.53,0:08:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother was a weak woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.47,0:08:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When she found out her beloved man \Nwas making love to other woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.02,0:08:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,she stepped aside voluntarily, \Nin favor of that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.49,0:09:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,However, mother never managed \Nto overcome the grief of that parting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.62,0:09:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She cried. She cried. She kept crying because she forgot \Nany other way to pass time than crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.08,0:09:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And this way, eventually, \Nmom left me alone in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.49,0:09:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the kind of woman she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.55,0:09:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Kind, affectionate...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.01,0:09:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But thus also weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo, parting is a ruthless affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.45,0:09:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the kinder one's heart is, \Nthe more kindness she needs{I know this is wrong but I don't see other way to repeat "kind" twice in this sentence while still making sense}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.02,0:09:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as affection, the more affectionate she is. \NBut that also means she is more frail{/ deeply vulnerable}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.67,0:09:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why, Daigo, when the bitter parting arrives, \NI trust you to look after Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.04,0:09:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, Oka has, among her amazing qualities{/ in addition to her amazing talents}, \Nthis faculty for being boundlessly affectionate and kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.36,0:09:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like my mom did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.23,0:09:45.25,Sign,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.77,0:09:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My friends, thank you all for coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.28,0:09:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In preparation to your departure that is just a week away, \Nthere is something I deem necessary for all of you to know.{/ I absolutely wanted to tell to all of our personnel.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,To be precise, it is a story about our great predecessors, \Nso strong for their time, it's hard to believe even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.55,0:10:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In May 1916{5th year of Taisho}, on his first tour to US, \NKumagai Kazuya trounced Pan-American #1 Johnson.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.31,0:10:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He then achieved an impressive 5th place \Nin Pan-American rankings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.40,0:10:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, in June 1920{Taisho year 9},
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.54,0:10:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with Chieftain{maybe Tilden}, at that time nicknamed The Tennis Giant, \NShimizu Zenzo put up an unexpectedly close match.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.32,0:10:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then finally, what sparked a commotion over Japan{/ what surged the Japanese sensation} \Nin the world, was the emergence of Sato Jiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.76,0:10:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Year is 1932{Year 7 of Showa}. In Wimbledon, \Nhe trounced last year's champion American Wadd,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.71,0:10:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,advancing to the semi-finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.73,0:10:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Next year as well, \Nhe defeated Britain's number 1 Perry,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.20,0:10:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,giving rise to a world sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.74,0:10:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,From his 3rd position in rankings, \Nhe gleamed at the world with magnificence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.80,0:10:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan at that time \Nwas spurred by achievements of those men.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.06,0:10:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One after another, \Nnew tennis talents began emerging.{/ the new blood flocked into tennis.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.98,0:10:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The tendency persisted up to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.77,0:10:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, there is no doubt that Japan's position \Nin the world's top-class echelon is unwavering.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.07,0:10:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Japanese tennis world \Nhad to face 3 major tragedies following that success.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.16,0:11:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The first tragedy being Sato Jiro's suicide \Nby throwing himself overboard in Straits of Malacca.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.70,0:11:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason remains a mystery to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.00,0:11:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite his incredible genius, \Nhe remained a sensitive{/ vulnerable / subtle} fellow,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.67,0:11:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's said that the burden turned out too heavy \Nwhen the entire country put its expectations on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.67,0:11:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then comes the second tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.73,0:11:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,World War 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.80,0:11:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A young promising players is consequently a good soldier.{REALLY unsure, maybe it's something like "Because the succession chain broke between young promising players and experiensed players"}\NWe suffered many devastating blows because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.35,0:11:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the third tragedy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.89,0:11:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this one took place 5 years ago. \NIt's a relatively recent one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.77,0:11:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone present should either be acquainted \Nor even related with the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, this tragedy affected our main young hope \Nof post-war days, 2 promising players.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.99,0:11:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata Jin and Katsura Daigo \Nwere struck by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.17,0:12:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata and Katsura Daigo were both big game players, \Nso similar that there was no way to determine the best one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.22,0:12:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Both played on par with westerners, \Naspiring for the power tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.27,0:12:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And both put it strikingly into practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.52,0:12:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese tennis has once again appointed those two \Nas the golden pair in the vanguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.40,0:12:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then unleashed them on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.02,0:12:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was this very moment, \Nwhen the incident struck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.78,0:12:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The two were practicing like devils \Nfor that year's All-Japan championship.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.12,0:12:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In high school and college, \Nthey attended the same tennis club.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two were always together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.46,0:12:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one knew the other's strengths and weaknesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.71,0:12:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of that, they trained each other,\Ngrowing only stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.34,0:12:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They could play in full auto mode, \Nmaking perfect rivals while being best friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.55,0:12:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This one's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.52,0:12:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Like hell!{/ You're quick to judge!}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.27,0:13:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.99,0:13:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Struck by sudden spasms and fever of unidentified origin, \NMunakata was hospitalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.58,0:13:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Later that same day, \Nhe announced his retirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.29,0:13:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, just a day after, Katsura Daigo also abruptly \Ncut ties and disappeared, remaining missing even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.61,0:13:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was safe to assume he had retired as well.{/ De facto, it was effectively a retirement.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.36,0:13:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Spasms and fever of unidentified origin... \NWhat do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Literally that - the cause was never identified.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.09,0:13:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.59,0:13:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Retirement notice \Nwas the manifestation of Munakata's iron will.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.69,0:13:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We could do naught but submit to his will \Nthat we held in high regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.05,0:13:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,By collapsing on the court like that again, \Nhe would have tarnished the pride of a player,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.34,0:13:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which he'd never forgive himself for.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.60,0:13:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But why did Mr. Katsura too...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The retirement of best friend \Nwas perhaps too much a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.70,0:13:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, we can but to speculate about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.61,0:14:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,However, whatever tragedies may come at us, \Nthey won't ever make us give up tennis!{/ ever be able to take tennis away from us.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.12,0:14:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, even Munakata \Nsoon rose again{/ was revived} as a famous coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.62,0:14:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This way contributing to nurturing{guess, can't really figure that "sumanshisutsu" word} \Nthe young new talents!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.60,0:14:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot live in captivity \Nof those 10 or 20 last years!{Those 10 or 20 last years should not have a sway over us / seize us with fear!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we already had a long history \Nbefore those events!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.85,0:14:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the course of that history, \Nwe were, decisively, not the underdogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.79,0:14:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, colleagues, \Ngo to the US with your head held high!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.62,0:14:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As proud descendants of the strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.36,0:14:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one week left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.16,0:14:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why then, Coach, they won't discharge you \Nfrom the hospital even now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.94,0:14:42.96,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nishi{/Western} Medical University {Supplementary }Hospital{trust me, this sign will be fully shown in ep 9}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.45,0:14:48.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,Closed until tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.96,0:15:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.44,0:15:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A visit...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.19,0:15:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That won't be possible.{/ would be troublesome.}\NVisits time is until 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.36,0:15:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But... There's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.45,0:15:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Not possible. \NAt night, it may be a nuisance for other patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.99,0:15:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It opens at 7:30 in the morning. \NCome back tomorrow, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.16,0:15:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to see you now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.21,0:16:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.31,0:16:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You lied! You said they'll discharge you in one week. \NThis one week has passed long ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.04,0:16:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the case, Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.98,0:16:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I lied to you for the first time, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.61,0:16:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That was mean of me. \NCan you forgive me for that, Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.25,0:16:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you forgive me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.57,0:16:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You erred... \NDemon Coach erred for the first time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.91,0:16:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Is this the first time \Nyou see me making an error?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.30,0:16:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the very first time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.79,0:16:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll confess one more mistake while we're at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.71,0:16:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, we won't be able to go to America together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.09,0:16:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Detailed checkup will take just a bit more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.12,0:16:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.84,0:16:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, I will depart 4 or 5 days later than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.49,0:16:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it's over, I will follow you immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgive you. \NBecause you confessed it yourself, I trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.34,0:17:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust you, Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.95,0:17:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,More than anything else... \NOr anyone else, I trust you, Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.53,0:17:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.23,0:17:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting, Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.04,0:17:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.37,0:17:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nail clippers.\N- OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.75,0:17:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Cards{/ Trumps}.\N- Prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.16,0:17:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- Books to read before going to sleep.\N- Checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.61,0:17:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this a bit of an overkill? \NIt takes too much space!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.13,0:17:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- High socks, 1 pair.\N- Next!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.13,0:17:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oolong tea bags.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.92,0:17:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I really memo'd that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.13,0:17:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- Long coat.\N- Getting it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.97,0:17:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yacht parka.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.29,0:17:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta look for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.20,0:17:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Slim - 1 pair, corduroy - 2 pairs \Nblack and white - 1 pair of each.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.68,0:17:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even started yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.98,0:17:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What now? You expect to be in time \Nfor tomorrow's departure that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.20,0:17:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that why I called you for help?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.30,0:17:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're always like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.92,0:17:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What a nice weather it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea{/ gulf water} is sparkling!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.12,0:18:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin, you shouldn't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.79,0:18:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Wandering around while you're a patient{/ ill}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.94,0:18:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you yourself doing here? \NAlready done preparing for tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.58,0:18:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I postponed it. \NI have to tend to you until you're better.{/ One shouldn't leave a sick man behind.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.09,0:18:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be selfish!\NYou're letting down many people.{/ Don't say nonsense! You were selected for a reason.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.61,0:18:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot go. \NI'm not leaving without Jin.{/ I can only go together with Jin.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.34,0:18:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't leave, can you, Jin?\NTherefore I'm staying as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.45,0:18:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Jin, can I already \Nstart calling you brother in public?{/ in those precarious circumstances?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.86,0:18:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Though I understand you'll hardly ever forgive my dad \Nfor betraying your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we had different mothers, \Nyou're the only person I can call a sister.{for god's sake I give up to make this convo consequtive and not out-of-blue}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.81,0:18:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Like this, Jin?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.29,0:18:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they are. \NYes, come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.30,0:18:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, here. It's from all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.93,0:19:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, we'll go there one step ahead of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.89,0:19:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But we still expect you \Nto join us as soon as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And you as well, Midorikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.89,0:19:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.47,0:19:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The main objective of this tour \Nis to introduce you to the power tennis of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.48,0:19:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of victory, \Ntry to scout strong points of many opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.59,0:19:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, pay attention \Nto your own weak points.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.88,0:19:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.32,0:19:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, then go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.45,0:19:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.03,0:19:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ranko, the blinds...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.10,0:19:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.04,0:19:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay strong, Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.78,0:19:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.80,0:19:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Then, in lieu of Hiromi, \NI'll be visiting Coach every day!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.09,0:19:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Count on you, Maki.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.98,0:19:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Have no worries!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.87,0:19:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, either way, I think, in the course of next week, \NI'll set out to follow you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.69,0:19:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't forget your camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.94,0:19:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.99,0:20:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We're off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.95,0:20:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We're off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.99,0:20:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget the souvenirs!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.87,0:20:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.57,0:20:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,January 15 \NGoing to US
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.29,0:20:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Should be onboard the plane by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.36,0:20:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ranko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.36,0:20:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.97,0:20:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you change the water in the vase{/ for the flowers}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.68,0:20:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.93,0:21:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jin!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.24,0:21:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.86,0:21:27.35,Sign,,0,0,0,,Oka, aim for the ace!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.35,0:21:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.72,0:21:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.25,0:21:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.17,0:21:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He was 27 years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.92,0:21:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He was only 27 years old!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.55,0:23:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Aikawa Maki.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.98,0:23:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They went to New York for overseas tour!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.07,0:23:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Clueless Hiromi is greeted by a completely new coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.95,0:23:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And a worldwide famous coach at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.35,0:23:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But Hiromi still believes \NCoach Munakata is joining them any day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.07,0:23:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.08,0:23:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, why did you have to pass away?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.84,0:23:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi is still waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.39,0:23:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Next episode:\NOverseas tour without Coach
